# @homeos/web — environment template (Vite)
# Copy to a local env file, then edit:   cp env.example .env.local
# Vite loads .env.local (and .env) automatically; both are gitignored. NEVER commit real tokens.
#
# IMPORTANT — these are NOT new secrets. Each token must be an EXACT COPY of the matching token in
# apps/server/.env, because the browser sends it as the Bearer and the server compares it byte-for-byte.
# A mismatch = 401 (the screen shows its error/empty state).
#
#   VITE_HOMEOS_READ_TOKEN      ==  READ_TOKEN      (server)
#   VITE_HOMEOS_MESSAGES_TOKEN  ==  MESSAGES_TOKEN  (server)
#   VITE_HOMEOS_WRITE_TOKEN     ==  WRITE_TOKEN     (server)
#
# These are read by Vite at DEV and BUILD time and baked into the static bundle — they are family-shared
# secrets in one public bundle, NOT real per-user auth (deferred). Treat the bundle as readable.

# ── Local run modes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# UI-only (layout / theme / RTL): just `pnpm --filter @homeos/web dev` → http://localhost:5173.
#   No tokens needed; the data-backed cards (events board, "recent ingestion" feed) show their
#   loading/error/empty states. That's expected without a backend.
#
# Real data: the dev server has NO proxy and the API server has NO CORS, so a split (5173 → 3000)
#   is blocked by the browser. Use SAME-ORIGIN instead:
#     1. set the tokens below (= the server's tokens)
#     2. pnpm --filter @homeos/web build      # bakes the tokens into apps/web/dist
#     3. pnpm --filter @homeos/server dev      # serves that dist same-origin at :3000
#     4. open http://localhost:3000  (NOT :5173)
#   Leave VITE_HOMEOS_API_BASE unset for same-origin.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Base URL of the @homeos/server API. UNSET / empty = same origin (the server serves apps/web/dist).
# Set ONLY for a split deploy where the API lives on a different origin (then the server needs CORS).
# VITE_HOMEOS_API_BASE=

# Family read token for the Bearer-gated GET /events (the board). MUST equal the server's READ_TOKEN.
VITE_HOMEOS_READ_TOKEN=

# Distinct token for GET /messages — the raw inbound feed behind the Connections "recent ingestion"
# card (#135/#182). MUST equal the server's MESSAGES_TOKEN. NO read-token fallback (separate privilege):
# unset ⇒ that card 401s to its empty/error state, the rest of the screen renders fine.
VITE_HOMEOS_MESSAGES_TOKEN=

# Distinct write token for POST /events (the Add-event form). MUST equal the server's WRITE_TOKEN.
# Unset ⇒ adding events is disabled (the server answers 503). Optional for read-only browsing.
VITE_HOMEOS_WRITE_TOKEN=
